File: platform/mcp-server/src/adapter-files.ts, lines 192-199.

Current code:
```
const deleteExecFile = async (filename: string): Promise<void> => {
  try {
    await unlink(join(getAdaptersDir(), filename)).catch(() => {});
  } catch {
    log.warn(`Failed to delete exec file: ${filename}`);
  }
};
```

The .catch(() => {}) on the unlink promise swallows all rejections, converting them to resolved promises. The outer try-catch never fires, making the log.warn on line 197 dead code.

Fix: remove the .catch(() => {}) so unlink rejections propagate to the outer catch block, which already has the correct log.warn. The function's JSDoc says 'Fire-and-forget — logs on failure' but the logging never executes.
